summary: This document is a preparation memo for Assistant U.S. Attorneys and a Special Agent/Detective regarding a witness's upcoming trial testimony. It outlines the witness's previously undisclosed, clarifying, or different recollections about being interviewed by the FBI in approximately 2007 regarding Jeffrey Epstein, and her belief about her appearance at the time.

persons.name: Jeffrey Epstein
persons.context: The witness was asked about him by FBI agents during an interview around 2007.

persons.name: Maxwell
persons.context: The witness does not remember the FBI agents asking her any questions about this individual.

events.title: FBI Interview of Witness
events.description: The witness was interviewed by FBI agents, who asked her questions about Jeffrey Epstein.

keyFacts: A witness was interviewed by the FBI about Jeffrey Epstein around 2007.
The witness does not recall the FBI agents asking her any questions about Maxwell during that interview.
The witness believes she looked 18 years old when she was going to Jeffrey Epstein's house.
